Post-Match Reflections: Buehler called the outing 'unacceptable,' but teammate Freddie Freeman defended his performance.
Dodgers manager Dave Roberts noted that while Buehler's command was an issue, he saw positives in his pitching.
Others: The Dodgers are looking for a viable No. 2 starter as October approaches, with Yoshinobu Yamamoto set to return from the injured list.
Buehler has struggled in the first inning this season, with a 9.69 ERA, and has faced consistency issues.
